{
  "text": "For a composition \u03b1 = (n 1 , . . . , n k ), we denote \u03bb(\u03b1) the unique partition of n obtained by reordering in decreasing order the n i . Then we have this well known result: W I and W J are conjugated under S n if and only if \u03bb(\u03b1 I ) = \u03bb(\u03b1 J ) (see [CITATION_1] , Proposition 2.3.8).",
